### Notification API Testing Collection
### Base URL: http://localhost:5002/v1/notifications
### NOTE: Replace {{authToken}} with your actual JWT token
### You can get the token by logging in first

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5002
@authToken = YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### ============================================
### SETUP: Login to get auth token
### ============================================

# @name login
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### ============================================
### 1. CREATE NOTIFICATION (New Schema)
### ============================================

# @name createNotification
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "modelName": "Order",
  "modelId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439011",
  "clientId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439012",
  "cpIds": ["507f1f77bcf86cd799439013"],
  "message": "Your order #12345 has been confirmed",
  "category": "Order",
  "metadata": {
    "orderNumber": "12345",
    "status": "confirmed"
  }
}

### ============================================
### 2. CREATE NOTIFICATION (Legacy Format)
### ============================================

# @name createNotificationLegacy
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/legacy
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "modelName": "Booking",
  "modelId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439014",
  "message": "Your booking has been updated",
  "category": "Booking"
}

### ============================================
### 3. GET ALL NOTIFICATIONS (with pagination)
### ============================================

# @name getAllNotifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications?page=1&limit=10&sortBy=createdAt:desc
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get notifications filtered by category
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications?category=Order&page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get notifications filtered by model
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications?modelName=Order&modelId=507f1f77bcf86cd799439011
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get unread notifications only
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications?isRead=false&page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get read notifications only
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications?isRead=true&page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ============================================
### 4. GET MY NOTIFICATIONS (Current User)
### ============================================

# @name getMyNotifications
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/my
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get my notifications with pagination
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/my?page=1&limit=10&sortBy=createdAt:desc
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ============================================
### 5. GET NOTIFICATIONS BY CATEGORY
### ============================================

# @name getNotificationsByCategory
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/category/Order
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get by Booking category
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/category/Booking
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get by Payment category
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/category/Payment
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ============================================
### 6. GET NOTIFICATIONS BY MODEL
### ============================================

# @name getNotificationsByModel
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/model/Order/507f1f77bcf86cd799439011
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Get by Booking model
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/model/Booking/507f1f77bcf86cd799439014
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ============================================
### 7. GET UNREAD COUNT
### ============================================

# @name getUnreadCount
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/unread-count
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ============================================
### 8. GET SPECIFIC NOTIFICATION BY ID
### ============================================

# @name getNotificationById
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/507f1f77bcf86cd799439015
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ============================================
### 9. MARK NOTIFICATION AS READ
### ============================================

# @name markAsRead
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/507f1f77bcf86cd799439015/read
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ============================================
### 10. MARK ALL NOTIFICATIONS AS READ
### ============================================

# @name markAllAsRead
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/mark-all-read
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "userId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439012",
  "userRole": "client"
}

### ============================================
### 11. UPDATE NOTIFICATION
### ============================================

# @name updateNotification
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/507f1f77bcf86cd799439015
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "message": "Updated message: Your order has been shipped",
  "metadata": {
    "orderNumber": "12345",
    "status": "shipped",
    "trackingNumber": "TRACK123456"
  }
}

### ============================================
### 12. DELETE SPECIFIC NOTIFICATION
### ============================================

# @name deleteNotification
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/507f1f77bcf86cd799439015
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ============================================
### 13. DELETE NOTIFICATIONS BY MODEL
### ============================================

# @name deleteNotificationsByModel
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/model/Order/507f1f77bcf86cd799439011
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### ============================================
### TESTING SCENARIOS
### ============================================

### Scenario 1: Create multiple notifications for testing
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "modelName": "Order",
  "modelId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439020",
  "message": "Test notification 1 - Order placed",
  "category": "Order"
}

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "modelName": "Order",
  "modelId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439020",
  "message": "Test notification 2 - Payment received",
  "category": "Order"
}

###
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "modelName": "Booking",
  "modelId": "507f1f77bcf86cd799439021",
  "message": "Test notification 3 - Booking confirmed",
  "category": "Booking"
}

### Scenario 2: Error testing - Invalid notification ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/invalid-id-format
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### Scenario 3: Error testing - Missing required fields
POST {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

{
  "message": "This should fail - missing required fields"
}

### Scenario 4: Error testing - Unauthorized access (no token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications/my

### ============================================
### ROLE-BASED TESTING
### ============================================

### Test as Admin (should see all notifications)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{adminAuthToken}}

### Test as Client (should see only their notifications)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{clientAuthToken}}

### Test as Content Provider (should see only their notifications)
GET {{baseUrl}}/v1/notifications?page=1&limit=10
Authorization: Bearer {{cpAuthToken}}
